 Super Falcons. Photo; TWITTER/NGSUPERFALCONS  The Nigeria Football Federation (NFF) says the search for a ‘quality coach’ for the Super Falcons has ended. The football body said that ‘paper work’ is the only thing delaying the announcement of a new trainer.  Pinnick had revealed recently that the NFF had set aside an undisclosed amount of money to pay the incoming head coach of the Super Falcons for a number of years.  “We have plenty of them, and I want the NFF to show some level of understanding in this regard by listening to my advice,” Mabo stated. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .